abstract: From The Utica Observer. Jan. 27. The New-York Times prints to-day a very good picture of the young New-York City Republican representative in the Assembly the Hon. James R. Sheffield. Although born in Dubuque, Mr. Sheffield is "a Utica boy," for he was reared in this town. It is not a dozen years since he sat in the Utica Free Academy, enjoying the friendship of all the boys.
